Package com.example.backend.entity

Class User

java.lang.Object
com.example.backend.entity.User
@Entity(name="User") public class User extends Object
The User class represents the user entity in the system. It contains information about a user such as name, email, password, phone, address, image, and a description of the user. This class is annotated as a JPA Entity, indicating that it is a JPA managed entity and is mapped to the "user" table in the "zti_project" schema of the relational database. The class fields represent the columns in the "user" table, with the OneToMany relationships indicating that a single user can be associated with multiple user messages and flights. The UserBuilder nested class provides a builder pattern for creating a User instance.
